Sgurr Fiona (An Teallach)

Hear pronunciation Press to hear pronunciation

Sgurr Fiona is the finer of the two Munro summits on the magnificent ridge of An Teallach. It is a perfect pyramid of rock and guards the beginning of the trickiest part of the traverse.

 You have not climbed Sgurr Fiona (An Teallach).

Region: Ullapool

Altitude: 1060 metres

Users' Rating:
  • Currently 4.53/5
Rating: 4.5/5 (89 votes cast)

You must be registered and signed-in to vote

Detailed route description and map

An Teallach traverse, Dundonnell

Other routes and challenges

For those who dislike exposure and don't want even to follow the bypass routes, the tricky section of ridge can be avoided entirely by ascending via the route given as far as Sgurr Fiona, and then reversing the route back to the start.
